President Muhammadu Buhari, on Monday, met with the Governor of the Central Bank of Nigeria (CBN), Godwin Emefiele, at the Presidential Villa Abuja. The CBN governor, who met with the President privately for the third time since the Naira swap crisis escalated across the country, did not speak to journalists when leaving the Presidential Villa. The reason for the visit was not known as at the time of filing this report, however, itâ€™s believed to be in connection to finding solution to the currency swap crisis.